Description: Regional West Medical Center School of Radiologic Technology is a school in Scottsbluff.
Full Description: For aspiring radiographers in Western Nebraska, the Regional West Medical Center (RWMC) School of Radiologic Technology (SORT) has programs to suit your needs. SORT offers a two-year degree program in Radiographer Education that prepares students for careers as technologists. It is one of the only programs of its kind in the state. Those who want to continue their education to achieve a bachelor’s degree in a related field, such as CT/MRI or Cardiovascular/Radiation Therapy Education, must attend a partner school like the University of Nebraska at Kearney or Chadron State College. Applicants to SORT must be high school graduates who are at least 18 years of age. They are required to submit the following documentation in order to be considered for admissions: official transcripts, SAT or ACT scores, and proof of completion of at least 35 hours of college credit in related fields. Financial aid is not available for students enrolled in the Radiographer Education program through SORT, unless they have certain military benefits. Students who are enrolled at SORT partner schools may be eligible for financial aid through them. If you see a future for yourself as a health care professional, in a hospital or clinic setting, Regional West Medical Center School of Radiologic Technology might be a perfect fit for you.

Description: TeleTrust is a telecommunications startup that focuses on leveraging IPs in identity and data services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: TeleTrust is an early stage telecommunications startup, funded by the founders and by early angel investors. Based in the Seattle area, TeleTrust is focused on leveraging unique IP in identity services and telecommunications data.  TeleTrust's goal is to be a "trusted partner in telecommunications, mobility solutions, mobile application development and products built around trusted openly-sourced telecommunications data and line connectivity." TeleTrust's founders include Eric Rock, former elected Chair of the National LIDB (Line Information Database) Forum, co-creator of the Caller ID / Caller Name system nationwide, and owner of significant telecommunications and line connectivity product lines at Illuminet, VeriSign Telco Services Group (CSG) and Transaction Network Services (TNS). The other founder of TeleTrust is Ned Hayes, a mobile application and identity management expert who has formerly worked at Kiha Software on mobile applications, and has led product ideation at Adobe Systems' Advanced Technology Labs.  TeleTrust is unique as a small startup in that they are already members of the Open Identity Exchange (OIX) certification group for telco services, a body that emerged from Open Identity circles and was organized by the executive director of the Open Identity Foundation.

If requirements and practices change over time, the software can change as well, since you own it. We love having end-users have a say in the design and development process. The outcome is often easier and more intuitive for those who will use the software every day. Why BG Software? We understand there is no one size fits all fix for software. We take the time to get to know your unique situation.  Not only have we been building, maintaining and enhancing custom software systems for over 13 years, we also create systems that are scalable and easily adjustable to evolve with your project. Our process typically involves first meeting with your team to learn more about your primary need.  We then put together a plan to find the right technologies, software architects, and quality assurance teams to launch your project/program. A custom application is then created to fit your specific needs. What We Do Every building and every business is unique. The software which monitors them should be, too. Our software team specializes in providing tailored solutions that fit client needs and specifications. We specialize in custom software and database design, application development, systems integration, automation services, and authentication, as well as tools for data: transfer, processing, retrieval, management, maintenance, and storage. By utilizing open-source and commercial technologies to implement industry-proven software architectures, we deliver efficient, cost-effective solutions with an unmatched level of client support.

Description: YogaBlue - Yoga Classes at Pasadena, CA.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At YogaBlue we believe in focusing on our local community, making people feel connected and giving them a sense of purpose and belonging. We strive to provide excellent service and a memorable experience by focusing on the individual, communicating on a first name basis and making a lifelong connection. Promoting the philosophies of yoga, we believe in developing trust and focusing on one's overall sense of wellbeing. This includes balancing one's physical health, mental awareness and spiritual guidance. Our studios are a safe haven and refuge from the outside world. We have a genuine compassion for each student's welfare and focus on being a consistent variable in a very inconsistent world. We provide an escape from these outside influences and focus on creating a grounded sanctuary where people can interact with one another freely. The name YogaBlue is derived from the fifth chakra, which is considered a force center in the body. This chakra focuses on speech, communication and truth. Known as a relaxing color, blue has a soothing effect on the central nervous system and thyroid. Balancing the chakra helps increase wisdom and clarity, allowing enhanced communication and self-expression. YogaBlue is committed to teaching yoga to everyone, regardless of age or gender. We focus on individual growth, exploration and seek to allow students to become more at ease and "one" with their bodies. All our instructors are unique in their teaching principles and we provide a diverse schedule of classes ranging from Yoga Basics, Restorative, Yang/Yin, Therapy with Breath Work, Prenatal, Postnatal, Heat Flow and Detox. Our studios maintain a temperature between 75 to 90 degrees, at the discretion of each teacher and class, allowing students to relax in the warmth and comfort of this restorative discipline. YogaBlue focuses on balancing strength, awareness, peace and health. This comforting atmosphere helps celebrate and honor inner strength through the practice of yoga, which helps restore the body and calm the mind.

With almost 20 years experience in the telecommunications industry, Paul Markland saw a growing demand for a full service interconnect company. The industry was lacking quality service for business telephone systems, data network installations, paging and background music systems. To satisfy these demands P.M.Communications was founded. Providing a full range of business communication services. P.M.Communications steadily grew into a successful full-service interconnect. Today P.M.Communications resides in its own commercial building, consisting of staff offices, a testing lab and a warehouse facility. In their lab they set up and burn in major hardware and software components to insure onsite reliability. They keep their warehouse stocked with vital components and replacement parts to insure rapid and efficient service. P.M.Communications specializes in the installation and service of small and large business telephone systems, voicemail, auto attendants, VoIP networking, PRI and T1 services, DID routing, data/network cabling, fiber optic and underground cable installations, paging and background music systems. Their clients include government facilities, real estate agencies, stock brokerages, automotive dealerships, healthcare facilities, sports complexes, country clubs, churches, schools, airline agencies, non-profit organizations, all types of contractors and many other high tech businesses who demand custom designed communication solutions. Their client list continues to grow due to their strong commitment to superior service, award winning telephone systems, clean, reliable installations implemented by highly trained and skilled professional technicians. P.M.Communications also has an office staffed with polite and professional personnel to answer your calls and give you the personal attention your business deserves. They also provide live technical support and 24/7 emergency dispatch service. P.M.Communications carefully listens to the customers needs, then their experienced system designers create a custom fit system to match the customer's requirements. They design affordable telephone systems to match any telecommunications requirement and budget.

Shamrock Structures is a drug discovery research services company that provides pharmaceutical researchers with access to unrivaled Tech.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Shamrock Structures was founded in 2003 by Flavin Ventures, an early stage venture capital and management group for innovative Midwestern life sciences companies focused on drug discovery. Shamrock Structures is a drug discovery research services company that provides pharmaceutical researchers with access to unrivaled technologies and expertise for three dimensional protein structure determinations. Possessing protein structure information empowers researchers to conduct ‘structure-based drug discovery. Protein crystallography is the science of determining the structures of therapeutically relevant proteins at the atomic scale, the most basic level of our biological make-up. There are approximately 100,000 different proteins in the human body. They are the building blocks of life and play critical roles in our biology by doing the body’s work. Since proteins are what drugs target, being able to see them and how a drug interacts with them structurally enables researchers to use a computer-aided, structure-based approach to design and build better drugs that bind more tightly into a protein’s active site like a ‘key into a lock’.
